sections.code_coverage_prose:
\textbf{NO.}  A collider-specific grep over \texttt{quarkConstraints/},
\texttt{qcd/}, \texttt{flavorConstraints/}, \texttt{neutrinos/},
\texttt{yukawa/}, \texttt{warpConfig/}, \texttt{solvers/},
\texttt{scanParams/}, and \texttt{tests/} found no \(T_{5/3}\),
\(X_{5/3}\), VLQ, top-partner, collider, or LHC direct-search implementation.
The adjacent code is low-energy RS machinery: \texttt{quarkConstraints/modern/scan.py:1230}
maps \(\Lambda_{\mathrm{IR}}\) to \(M_{KK}\), \texttt{quarkConstraints/modern/scan.py:1254}
stores that scan-point \(M_{KK}\), \texttt{quarkConstraints/couplings.py:103}
defines mass-basis KK-gluon couplings, \texttt{quarkConstraints/couplings.py:116}
describes the enhanced 5D KK-gluon coupling, and
\texttt{quarkConstraints/deltaf2.py:1} identifies the implemented exclusion
slice as a tree-level KK-gluon-inspired \(\Delta F=2\) benchmark.  The
matching layer itself notes at \texttt{quarkConstraints/modern/matching.py:240}
that it is not a full operator-complete EFT/RG package.
